The Proposal: -

Amravati district. Mamdapur Ta. Varud (Scheme Code-20056232) The original budget of the tap water supply scheme was prepared by the Executive Engineer, Rural Water Supply Department, Zilla Parishad, Amravati vide Reference No. Technical approval is provided under Section 2. The estimated cost of the project is Rs. 46.83 is the focus. Also, Reference No. 1 under Rs. 37.47 Attention Admin approval is provided for such a modest price. Reference No. 5 of the Department. A letter dated 24.01.2023 has given ex-post facto approval to the bid for the additional rate of the scheme. Also, the Chief Executive Officer, Zilla Parishad, Amravati proposed to give revised administrative approval to the proposed tap water supply scheme vide Reference Letter No. 4 here. The letter dated 26.09.2025 has been submitted to the government. Reference No. 3 here. Under the letter dated 01.08.2025, the government was under consideration to grant revised administrative approval to the price as per the revised technical approval given by the Executive Engineer, Rural Water Supply Department, Zilla Parishad, Amravati.
The government's decision:

Under the "Jal Jeevan Mission Programme," Dr. Mamdapur Ta. The ASS tap water supply scheme has been awarded a tender price of Rs.2,000 / - subject to the following conditions, namely, acceptance of tender at the higher rate of Goods and Services Tax (GST) and increase in the cost of the scheme due to technical changes. The revised price of 39.34 lakh (Rupees forty-nine lakh thirty-four thousand only) is being approved by the Administrator.
Government Decision No: Suprama-2025 / P.No.735 / Papu-13
1) The CEO / Chief Engineer will be responsible for completing all the remaining works within the prescribed time frame at the above mentioned revised cost.
2) The original administrative approval agreed upon for the scheme as well as the terms and conditions mentioned while granting the revised technical approval should be strictly adhered to.

3) On completion of the scheme, it should be handed over to the concerned Gram Panchayat. The concerned Gram Panchayat / Zilla Parishad shall be responsible for taking over the scheme within one month from the date of receipt of intimation from the concerned Executive Engineer, Rural Water Supply Department, Zila Parishad that the scheme has actually been completed. Immediately after the actual completion of the scheme, a joint inspection of the scheme should be conducted by the concerned Executive Engineer, Zilla Parishad and concerned Gram Panchayat officials and any defects found in such inspection should be corrected before handing over the scheme.

4) The Gram Panchayat / Zilla Parishad concerned shall not receive any assistance from the Government for the implementation of the scheme, maintenance, repairs (subject to special modifications), depreciation in the scheme or renovation of machinery to meet the recurring expenditure incurred every year.
5) On completion of the scheme, it will be mandatory for the local body (concerned Gram Panchayat / Zila Parishad) to implement the scheme. The accounts of the scheme should also be closed.

6) A CAG report in 2013 shows that 21 per cent of water supply schemes in the state have been shut down due to poor maintenance / non-payment of electricity bills. In fact, in order to make the scheme financially viable, it will be the responsibility of the concerned Gram Panchayat / Zilla Parishad to increase the water tariff as per the requirement.
7) Action should be taken in accordance with the prevailing policy on extortion.
8) It shall be the responsibility of the Zilla Parishad that the present scheme shall not be revised under any circumstances.

9) Since administrative expenditure is not permissible under the Jal Jeevan Mission, it should be excluded if any administrative expenditure of 4% has been taken up in the revised budget of the scheme.
10) It should be ensured at the Zilla Parishad level that the tendering process of the scheme is carried out properly.
